/teaching-courses/course-listing/dpi-680">"Harvard Kennedy School \xe2\x80\x93 New Media and Public Action"</a>. Hks.harvard.edu<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2011-06-03</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AClay+Shirky&amp;rft.btitle=Harvard+Kennedy+School+%E2%80%93+New+Media+and+Public+Action&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.pub=Hks.harvard.edu&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hks.harvard.edu%2Fdegrees%2Fteaching-courses%2Fcourse-listing%2Fdpi-680&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.shirky.com/herecomeseverybody/2008/02/supernova-talk-the-internet-runs-on-love.html">The Internet Runs on Love: Here Comes Everybody</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20080313232735/http://www.shirky.com/herecomeseverybody/2008/02/supernova-talk-the-internet-runs-on-love.html">Archived</a> 2008-03-13 at the <a href="/wiki/Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine">Wayback Machine</a>., SuperNova Talk</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Shirky_2008_260.E2.80.93277-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Shirky_2008_260.E2.80.93277_11-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Shirky_2008_260.E2.80.93277_11-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Shirky, Clay (2008). <i>Here Comes Everybody</i>. USA: Penguin Books. pp.&#160;260\xe2\x80\x93277. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780143114949" title="Special:BookSources/9780143114949">9780143114949</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%